                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857 T53/31.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul General at
                            Halifax</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Halifax, Nova Scotia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mackay-Bennett cable that boat is due Halifax Thursday with bodies recovered from
                    wreck of the <hi rend="italic">Titanic</hi>. Are there any penalties necessary
                    preparatory to shipping bodies across border to New York?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ragsdale.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
